From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: WHO/CSR, 27 Apr 2000 [edited
<http://www.who.int/emc/outbreak_news/n2000/april/27apr2000.html>

Meningococcal disease in Saudi Arabia and the Netherlands - Update
Saudi Arabia-Update: Health authorities have reported a revised total of
225 cases, including 57 deaths since the Haj last month. Bacterial
investigations have now confirmed _Neisseria meningitidis_ serogroup A in
54 cases, serogroup W135 in 50 cases, and serogroup B in 1 case. The
situation is being closely monitored by the health authorities, with case
management and contact tracing in place.
Netherlands-Update: There have been 2 confirmed cases of _N. meningitidis_
serogroup W135 and 2 probable cases, including 1 death reported. Case
management and contact tracing are also being carried out.
Please see the previous report of meningococcal disease in these two
countries.
